These are the ones that I noticed. It&#x27;s absolutely possible that there are more issues.

These are taken from {{"x-revision": "2403ff885fd4"}}

h2. /2.0/repositories/{username}/{repo_slug}/commits
h3. GET
Accepts {{exclude}} and {{include}} "query" parameters. But the Swagger API specification&#x27;s {{parameters}} field is empty {{[]}}.

h3. POST
Accepts {{exclude}} and {{include}} "body" parameters. But the Swagger API specification&#x27;s {{parameters}} field is empty {{[]}}.

It should be something like:

{code}
#!json
"paths": {
  "/repositories/{username}/{repo_slug}/commits": {
    "get": {
      "parameters": [
        {
          "required": false,
          "in": "query",
          "type": "string",
          "name": "include"
        },
        {
          "required": false,
          "in": "query",
          "type": "string",
          "name": "exclude"
        }
      ]
    },
    "post": {
      "parameters": [
        {
          "required": false,
          "in": "body",
          "type": "string",
          "name": "include"
        },
        {
          "required": false,
          "in": "body",
          "type": "string",
          "name": "exclude"
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
{code}

h2. /2.0/repositories/{username}/{repo_slug}/commits/{revision}
h3. GET
Same as {{GET /2.0/repositories/{username}/{repo_slug}/commits}}

h3. POST
Same as {{POST /2.0/repositories/{username}/{repo_slug}/commits}}

h2. /2.0/repositories/{username}/{repo_slug}/downloads
h3. POST
Accepts  {{multipart/form-data}}. But the Swagger API specification doesn&#x27;t have {{consumes}} field.

It should be:

{code}
#!json
"paths": {
  "/repositories/{username}/{repo_slug}/downloads": {
    "post": {
      "consumes": [
        "multipart/form-data"
      ]
    }
  }
}
{code}

h2. /2.0/repositories/{username}/{repo_slug}/filehistory/{node}/{path}
h3. GET
Accepts {{fields}} "query" parameters. But the Swagger API specification&#x27;s {{parameters}} field doesn&#x27;t have it.

It should add:

{code}
#!json
{
  "required": false,
  "type": "string",
  "in": "query",
  "name": "fields"
}
{code}

h2. /2.0/repositories/{username}/{repo_slug}/forks
h3. POST
The {{post.parameters}} field in the Swagger API specification has duplicate {{username}} & {{repo_slug}}, because they are already present in {{parameters}} field.

h2. /2.0/repositories/{username}/{repo_slug}/hooks
h3. POST
Accepts "body" parameters. But the Swagger API specification&#x27;s {{parameters}} field is empty {{[]}}.

As per convention, it should be:

{code}
#!json
[
  {
    "required": true,
    "in": "body",
    "name": "_body"
  }
]
{code}

Also, {{schema}} should be added.

h2. /2.0/repositories/{username}/{repo_slug}/hooks/{uid}
h3. PUT
{{put.parameters}} has {{uid}}, but it&#x27;s already present in {{parameters}}. So it should be removed.

Also, it&#x27;s unclear which parameters it accepts. Probably just "body". In that case, need {{schema}} too.

h2. /2.0/repositories/{username}/{repo_slug}/issues/{issue_id}
h3. PUT
Accepts "body" parameters. But the Swagger API specification&#x27;s {{parameters}} field is empty {{[]}}.

Should add that with {{schema}}

